## Overview
Learned how to exploit XSS when user input is placed inside JavaScript code.

## Key Concept
Input is reflected inside a JavaScript string:
var search = 'user_input';

## Challenge
Single quotes (') and backslashes (\) are escaped, preventing normal string breakouts.

## Exploitation Strategy
Instead of breaking the string, break out of the script context.

## Payload
</script><script>alert(1)</script>

## Steps
1. Identify input inside JavaScript
2. Observe escaping behavior
3. Close the existing script tag
4. Inject a new script tag
5. Execute JavaScript payload

## Insight
When direct injection is blocked, changing context (from JS string to HTML script) can still lead to execution.
